{# ── Architecture diagram ─────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-200 mb-4">How it works</h2>
  <pre class="card p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
 ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
 │        Hōzō Controller          │  (your always-on machine)
 │                                 │
 │  Scheduler ──► Job runner       │
 │                    │            │
 │          Wake-on-LAN packet     │
 │                    │            │
 └────────────────────┼────────────┘
                      │ SSH / WoL
                      ▼
 ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
 │       Remote NUC / Beelink      │  (sleeps until backup time)
 │                                 │
 │  Wakes  ──►  USB drive spins up │
 │              syncoid runs       │
 │              verify snapshot    │
 │              shutdown           │
 └─────────────────────────────────┘
                      │
                      ▼
             ZFS pool on USB drive
             (offsite-ready replica)
  </pre>
</section>

